Initialization script for the hardware usage reporter daemon 'celebid'.
It creates a daemon to run in the background. The daemon sends hardware usage and process info to a database defined in the celebi.config file.

usage: celebi <argument>

argument:
    -s, --start     start the celebid daemon
    -k, --kill      stop an running celebid daemon
    -h, --help      displays this help text

Output of the celebid daemon sent to 'celebid.log'
Lock file found at '/tmp/celebid.lock'

Verified versions:
    Debian GNU/Linux v.10

